time complexity: O(min(m, n))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:
The solution iterates through the characters of both strings simultaneously using two nested loops. If a '#' character is found in either string, the function returns false immediately, as it means the strings are not equal after removing the '#' characters. Otherwise, it compares the characters at corresponding positions in the strings until either string becomes empty. Since the strings have the same length, the time complexity is O(min(m, n)), where m and n are the lengths of the strings s and t, respectively. The space complexity is O(1) because the function only uses a constant amount of space. The energy implications are low because the function only performs simple comparisons and does not consume significant energy.

